Question.TranslatedText:
Pump Upgrade:&nbsp;Blood pump replaced for more efficient blood pump (Change Impella CP to Impella 5.5)
Mechanical replacement: Blood pump replaced for failure or suspected failure of normal mechanical operation
Thrombosis / coagulopathy: Device exchange primarily indicated by clot burden or coagulation derangement
Hemolysis: Device exchange primarily indicated by center-specific markers of hemolysis (for example, plasma free hemoglobin, lactate dehydrogenase, haptoglobin or bilirubin)
Equipment longevity / center protocol: Device exchange indicated by center-specific protocol regarding longevity of use without evidence of other derangement.&nbsp;
Entire circuit replaced following temporary transition to bypass: Device exchanged during whole circuit exchange following temporary transition of patient mechanical support to cardiopulmonary bypass&nbsp;
